This file lists all third-party dependencies used by Vela Slides,
their licenses, and how they are consumed. This serves as a
software bill of materials (SBOM) for IP due diligence purposes.


Runtime Dependencies (Claude.ai Artifact Sandbox)
-------------------------------------------------

These libraries are provided by the Claude.ai artifact runtime
environment and are NOT bundled with Vela Slides:

  React 18+
    License: MIT
    Source:  https://github.com/facebook/react
    Usage:   UI framework (useState, useReducer, useEffect, etc.)

  lucide-react 0.383.0
    License: ISC
    Source:  https://github.com/lucide-icons/lucide
    Usage:   Icon components (ChevronLeft, Maximize2, Download, etc.)


Runtime Dependencies (CDN-loaded)
---------------------------------

These libraries are loaded dynamically from CDN at runtime,
only when specific features are used:

  html2canvas 1.4.1
    License: MIT
    Source:  https://github.com/niklasvh/html2canvas
    CDN:     https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/html2canvas/1.4.1/html2canvas.min.js
    Usage:   Slide screenshot capture for AI visual context and
             alternatives generation. Loaded on-demand, not bundled.

  Google Fonts (Sora, DM Sans, Space Mono)
    License: SIL Open Font License 1.1
    Source:  https://fonts.google.com
    Usage:   Typography via CSS @import. No fonts are bundled.


External API
------------

  Anthropic Messages API (v1)
    Endpoint: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages
    Model:    claude-sonnet-4-20250514
    Usage:    AI features (Vera chat, improve, quick edit, alternatives).
              Calls are made client-side using the user's own Claude.ai
              session. No API keys are stored or distributed with Vela.
    Note:     AI features require the user's own Claude.ai subscription.
              Vela does not proxy, store, or relay any API credentials.


Build Dependencies (Python stdlib only)
---------------------------------------

The build toolchain (concat.py, assemble.py, validate.py) uses
only Python standard library modules:

  json, sys, os, re, pathlib, textwrap, datetime

No pip packages are required. No node_modules. No bundler.


Dependency Summary
------------------

  Total runtime deps:    3 (React, lucide-react, html2canvas)
  Total build deps:      0 (Python stdlib only)
  Copyleft licenses:     0
  Restrictive licenses:  0
  All licenses:          MIT, ISC, SIL OFL 1.1 — all permissive

No dependency imposes copyleft, viral, or disclosure obligations
on Vela Slides or its users.
